# Universal Image Defaults

When writing, rewriting, reviewing, or generating prompts for image models, use this as the default unless the user explicitly asks for darkness, night, gloom, murk, horror, or low-key lighting:

> Clear, bright, full normal daytime lighting by default. Not dim, murky, grimy, muddy, gloomy, shadow-choked, underexposed, dusk-like, night-like, or dark. Prefer readable, coherent, visually organized images with clean composition, clear separation of groups, concise high-contrast text, and attractive balanced color. Favor clarity over murky cinematic drama.

For OpenAI image models, including `gpt-image-2`, make this explicit in prompts rather than assuming the model will infer it. If a serious, dramatic, political, symbolic, or conflict scene is requested, keep the drama but preserve full daytime clarity and readability.
